## Component Patterns

### Component Definition Style
**IMPORTANT**: Always use normal functions instead of `React.FC` to define components:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Use normal functions
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
}

export function Component({ title, children }: ComponentProps) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}

// ❌ INCORRECT - Do not use React.FC
export const Component: React.FC<ComponentProps> = ({ title, children }) => {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
};
```

### Button Variants
The Button component supports multiple variants:
- `primary` - Main action buttons (violet gradient)
- `secondary` - Secondary actions
- `outline` - Bordered buttons
- `ghost` - Minimal styling
- `destructive` - Dangerous actions
- `success` - Positive actions
- `link` - Link-style buttons

